== Legal status ==
The Auckland Islands – as with all of New Zealand&#x27;s subantarctic islands – is a National Nature Reserve, afforded the highest possible level of protection under New Zealand law. In addition, a marine reserve encompasses all of the Auckland Islands territorial sea and internal waterways.

All of New Zealand&#x27;s subantarctic islands are managed by the Southland Conservancy of the Department of Conservation (DOC). Expedition party size, length of stay and landing on the islands are kept to a minimum. Entry is by permit only and applicants must undergo thorough pre-expedition quarantine checks.

When Andrew Fagan made a solo voyage there in a plywood yacht (and nearly added to the shipwreck tally), he described the DOC permitting process thus: 

